      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAINT RICO (2) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 6th at Gosford following on from a second place finish (30.05) at this track the start prior. Solid record here at the distance winning five races. Has performed well from this box with a win and five minor placings to his name from 10 starts. Tough to beat if on-song. NORDIC SHIRAZ (7) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by one length at Nowra in a handy 20.83 beating Mother Goose. Must be included in calculations. MISTER O'BRIEN (1) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
